data.title: Federal Reserve cut benchmark interest rate by quarter-percentage point, criticized for dissenting votes by Stephen Miran & Jeffrey R. Schmid. Wolfers criticizes Miran's 'utterly incoherent case for rate cuts,' pushes for more aggressive 50 bps cut. Split decision with majority lowering target range to 3.75% to 4%, Schmid dissenting in favor of holding rates steady. Wolfers connects Miran's move to recent appointment by Trump.
data.description: The Federal Reserve cut its benchmark interest rate by a quarter-percentage point, landing the target range at 3.75% to 4%. The decision was accompanied by internal dissent and external criticism of Governor Stephen Miran's push for a larger 0.5% cut. Economist Justin Wolfers criticized Miran's rationale as incoherent and not convincing. The Federal Open Market Committee's vote of 10-2 displayed a split in monetary policy, with Miran advocating for a more aggressive cut and Kansas City Fed President Jeffrey R. Schmid dissenting in favor of holding rates steady. Wolfers directly linked Miran's actions to his appointment by President Trump. The full story can be found on Benzinga.com.

data.title: KnowBe4 research shows personalized phishing emails using company name are most effective in Q3 2025. Tampa, FL. Oct. 30, 2025.
data.description: In the latest Phishing Simulation Roundup for the third quarter of 2025, it was found that individuals were most likely to engage with emails that pretended to be from coworkers or mentioned internal systems or topics. The report, released on October 30, 2025, by KnowBe4, a globally recognized cybersecurity provider, highlighted that a significant number of people interacted with these types of phishing emails. The data from the roundup sheds light on the prevalent issue of phishing attacks and the tactics used to target individuals.

data.title: BWXT awarded $174 million naval nuclear fuel contract in September 2025 for U.S. Naval program.
data.description: BWX Technologies, Inc. (NYSE: BWXT) disclosed securing a lucrative contract under the U.S. Naval Nuclear Propulsion Program in September 2025. Valued at around $174 million, this contract, awarded on Sept. 10, 2025, pertains to the production of naval nuclear reactor fuel. Nuclear Fuel Services, Inc., a subsidiary of BWXT situated in Erwin, Tennessee, will be responsible for the manufacturing and delivery of the fuel for the Naval Reactors Program. The fuel and reactors produced by BWXT play a crucial role in powering the U.S. Navy's operations.

data.title: Federal Signal Corporation achieved 17% net sales growth and 24% operating income improvement with Q3 net sales of $555 million. Company outlook raised with adjusted EPS at $4.09-$4.17 and net sales between $2.10-$2.14 billion for 2025. Quarterly net income was $68.1 million, or $1.11 per diluted share, up from $53.9 million in the prior year. The new credit facility increased revolving credit capacity to $1.1 billion for potential growth opportunities. Acquisition of New Way for $396 million expected to close in Q4 2025. Company reported strong financial position and plans for dividends and stock repurchases.
data.description: Federal Signal Corporation reported financial results for the third quarter ended September 30, 2025. Net sales were $555 million, up 17% from the previous year, with operating income of $94 million, up 24%. GAAP diluted EPS was $1.11, up 28%. Adjusted EPS was $1.14, up 30%. Orders were $467 million, up 10%. The company raised its 2025 adjusted EPS outlook to $4.09-$4.17 and net sales outlook to $2.10-$2.14 billion. They also executed a new $1.5 billion credit facility. Consolidated net sales were $555 million, with net income of $68.1 million. The company funded dividends of $8.5 million and announced a $0.14 per share dividend for the fourth quarter of 2025. Federal Signal Corporation operates in two groups: Environmental Solutions and Safety and Security Systems. Further financial details are provided in the article: https://www.benzinga.com/pressreleases/25/10/c28550777/federal-signal-reports-exceptional-third-quarter-results-raises-full-year-outlook.

data.title: Patrick Industries, Inc. saw 6% increase in Q3 2025 net sales to $976 million, but net income dropped to $35 million.
data.description: Patrick Industries, a component solutions provider, reported its financial results for Q3 2025, with net sales increasing by 6% to $976 million. Operating income was $66 million, down from $74 million in Q3 2024, with a margin of 6.8%. Net income was $35 million compared to $41 million in the prior year. Adjusted EBITDA was $112 million versus $121 million in the same period last year. Cash flow from operations for the first nine months of 2025 was $199 million compared to $224 million for the same period in 2024. The company returned $13 million to shareholders through dividends. Total net liquidity was $779 million, with a net leverage ratio of 2.8x. Revenue by sector for Q3 2025 saw growth in RV (7%), Marine (11%), Powersports (12%), and Housing (1%). Patrick Industries mentioned operational investments to improve performance. The company's full-year outlook seems positive due to a strong balance sheet and cash flow generation. Note that forward-looking statements regarding the company's performance are included in the press release.

data.title: LDRA & TASKING introduce tools to analyze timing interference in multi-core apps, aiding developers in avoiding issues.
data.description: In WIRRAL, England, LDRA, a TASKING Company known for automated software verification and standards compliance, has introduced enhanced features to their LDRA tool suite. This update enables advanced analysis of timing coupling interference in multi-core architectures. This new capability supplements the existing data and control coupling tools, providing developers with increased understanding of multi-core behavior. By incorporating these enhancements, developers can more effectively address timing issues. These innovations represent LDRA's commitment to providing comprehensive solutions for software development.
